{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Plan-review run: PASS, 0 blocking, signed (key 412fa5372ad877e0, llm_ran=true — a real review). Triaged all 10 advisory + 2 overflow findings and REMEDIATED the valid spec-gap ones in the description: (P6) split compound 'and'-bundled ACs + removed vague 'clean'; (E2) headroom is now a named config knob verify.verify_window_headroom=0.8, not a literal; (E2) projected_output defined as len(chunk)*PER_FINDING_VERIFY_TOKENS; (E1) oversized-finding escalation base pinned to the RESOLVED verify model (models_at_or_above(resolved_verify_model)); (T4) added a pre-deletion verdict-parity gate + expand→contract back-out before deleting bespoke _run_passes/pass2_verify/verifier_cfg; (T4) BPMN import back-compat for legacy files lacking the per-step model attribute; (T2) the >budget test now also grounds the chars/4 safety margin; (G5/overflow) made the WS2→WS3 dependency explicit and committed to decomposing WS1–WS4 into child tickets (each separately plan-reviewed). T7 was an affirmation (docs already in scope) — no action. NOTE: the description changed materially after this PASS, so the signed attestation is now STALE; the binding gate is per-child review before claim — re-review the epic only if we intend to claim the epic itself. Next: decompose WS1–WS4."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782581295772869001,"uuid":"dc3877ee-7ec8-4cf4-a7af-1f2407bc8dae"}